<h1 class="c10" id="h.jfet3kl6km8z"><span>Feedback</span></h1>
<p class="c8"><span>Please submit feedback by emailing: </span><span class="c4 c12"><a class="c0" href="mailto:rialto-service@lists.stanford.edu">rialto-service@lists.stanford.edu</a></span><span>.</span></p>
<h1 class="c10" id="h.chrcoquq4bw7"><span>Introduction</span></h1>
<p class="c8"><span class="c18 c12">What is RIALTO?</span></p>
<p class="c8"><span class="c2">RIALTO is a research intelligence application built by Stanford Libraries.</span></p>
<p class="c8"><span class="c7">RIALTO is currently in the beta phase. We are working to refine our data collection pipeline. Please let us know if you notice differences between the RIALTO data and your own records.</span></p>
<p class="c8 c13"><span class="c2"></span></p>
<p class="c8"><span class="c12 c18">What is the RIALTO ORCID dashboard?</span></p>
<p class="c8"><span>The RIALTO ORCID dashboard provides information about </span><span><a class="c0" href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://guides.library.stanford.edu/orcid/register&amp;sa=D&amp;source=editors&amp;ust=1764629355078299&amp;usg=AOvVaw2fWyR9L4WIyHvSR_J-AXyX">ORCID iD-SUNet integration</a></span><span class="c2"> by Stanford researchers in order to improve ORCID adoption outreach efforts and enable Stanford stakeholders to measure compliance with internal and external adoption policies.</span></p>
<p class="c8 c13"><span class="c2"></span></p>
<p class="c8"><span class="c18 c12">Why is ORCID integration important?</span></p>
<p class="c8"><span class="c15">ORCID integration is critical to RIALTO data collection as integrating ORCID iDs with SUNets is the only way RIALTO systems become aware of the ORCID iDs of Stanford researchers and ORCID iDs are the primary means of discovering the works or Stanford researchers.</span></p>
<h1 class="c10" id="h.u5bn3twko6o2"><span class="c11">Dashboard Tabs</span></h1>
<p class="c8"><span>The </span><span>ORCID</span><span> Dashboard features two dashboard tabs: </span><span class="c12">ORCID Overview</span><span> and </span><span class="c12">ORCID Drill Down</span><span class="c2">.</span></p>
<p class="c8 c13"><span class="c2"></span></p>
