<h1 class="c10" id="h.ccn8senky2ab"><span class="c11">Data Sources</span></h1>
<ul class="c1 lst-kix_a9ymd1m0e888-0 start">
<li class="c8 c14 li-bullet-0"><span class="c2">ORCID iD-SUNet integration statistics harvested from the ORCID iD-SUNet integration at regular intervals.</span></li>
<li class="c8 c14 li-bullet-0">
<span class="c12">SUL-Pub</span><span>: A publication harvesting system that is managed by Stanford University Libraries, Digital Library Systems and Services. The system harvests publications from the Web of Science, PubMed, and Dimensions by querying combinations of Stanford researcher names and institutions (including prior institutions) as well as ORCiDs. The publications are then sent to researchers to approve or deny and publish to their </span><span class="c4"><a class="c0" href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://profiles.stanford.edu/&amp;sa=D&amp;source=editors&amp;ust=1764629355081082&amp;usg=AOvVaw0XRjbx80WRmaqap9pXjlCH">Stanford Profile</a></span><span class="c2">.</span>
</li>
</ul>
<h1 class="c10" id="h.a799khcsf67w"><span class="c11">Data Definitions</span></h1>
<ul class="c1 lst-kix_4tu3lpuc48s1-0 start"><li class="c8 c14 li-bullet-0">
<span class="c12">ORCID</span><span>: Researchers who have gone through the Stanford </span><span class="c4"><a class="c0" href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://guides.library.stanford.edu/orcid/register&amp;sa=D&amp;source=editors&amp;ust=1764629355081519&amp;usg=AOvVaw3V5bPB0VisaHpgUhDfu5oA">ORCID iD-SUNet integration</a></span><span class="c2"> to connect their ORCID iD to their SUNet.</span>
</li></ul>
<ul class="c1 lst-kix_4tu3lpuc48s1-1 start">
<li class="c8 c9 li-bullet-0">
<span class="c12">ORCID Only</span><span class="c2">: Researchers who have connected their ORCID iD to their SUNet, but they haven’t granted Update Permission.</span>
</li>
<li class="c8 c9 li-bullet-0">
<span class="c12">ORCID &amp; Update Permission</span><span>: Researchers who have connected their ORCID iD to their SUNet, and have also granted Stanford permission to update their ORCID record. Stanford systems can now push publications that they have approved in SUL-Pub to their </span><span class="c4"><a class="c0" href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://orcid.org/&amp;sa=D&amp;source=editors&amp;ust=1764629355082676&amp;usg=AOvVaw2cUVIFAgqJn0ObQneVhS4p">ORCID profile</a></span><span class="c2">.</span>
</li>
<li class="c8 c9 li-bullet-0">
<span class="c12">ORCID (All) = ORCID Only + ORCID &amp; Update Permission</span><span class="c2">: This dashboard setting includes all researchers who have an ORCID connected with their SUNet, regardless of whether they’ve granted Update Permission or not.</span>
</li>
</ul>
<ul class="c1 lst-kix_4tu3lpuc48s1-0">
<li class="c8 c14 li-bullet-0">
<span class="c12">No ORCID</span><span class="c15">: </span><span>Researchers who</span><span class="c15"> may or may not have an ORCID but</span><span> </span><span class="c15">have not gone through the Stanford </span><span class="c4 c15"><a class="c0" href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://guides.library.stanford.edu/orcid/register&amp;sa=D&amp;source=editors&amp;ust=1764629355083491&amp;usg=AOvVaw2fIANRqJyP2g_eLU56zkoi">ORCID iD-SUNet integration</a></span><span>. If they do have an ORCID, the </span><span class="c15">RIALTO systems </span><span>are not aware</span><span class="c15"> of it</span><span> until they complete the SUNet integration.</span>
</li>
<li class="c8 c14 li-bullet-0">
<span class="c12">School</span><span class="c2">: The primary Stanford school a researcher is affiliated with. In some cases, a researcher may have multiple affiliations. This dashboard only tracks their primary affiliation.</span>
</li>
<li class="c8 c14 li-bullet-0">
<span class="c12">Department</span><span class="c2">: The primary Stanford department a researcher is affiliated with. In some cases, a researcher may have multiple affiliations. This dashboard only tracks their primary affiliation. </span>
</li>
</ul>
<h1 class="c10" id="h.1fuz9k8v9xno"><span class="c11">Data Filters</span></h1>
<ul class="c1 lst-kix_zfubk05n23z1-0 start">
<li class="c8 c14 li-bullet-0">
<span class="c12">Dashboard Filters</span><span class="c2">: When selected, these filters update all charts and tables in the dashboard tab simultaneously.</span>
</li>
<li class="c8 c14 li-bullet-0">
<span class="c12">Table Filters</span><span class="c2">: When selected, these filters only update their adjacent, corresponding table.</span>
</li>
</ul>
